SECOND BRAIN AI AGENT
Product Requirements & Development Guide
Version 1.0  |  April 2026


1. Project Overview
The Second Brain AI Agent is a personal intelligence system designed to serve as an always-available, continuously learning knowledge partner. It ingests content from multiple sources, remembers conversations, learns user style and preferences over time, and proactively surfaces relevant information. The system is built around Claude (Anthropic) as the primary reasoning model, orchestrated via LangGraph, with full observability via LangSmith.

1.1 Vision
A Jarvis-style personal AI agent that:
Ingests and understands documents, websites, videos, and structured data
Remembers everything discussed and updates its knowledge over time
Learns the user's thinking style, preferences, and communication patterns
Proactively surfaces relevant information without being asked
Supports deep reasoning and exploration with reinforcement learning capabilities
Operates with full observability, traceability, and a control plane for governance

1.2 Core Principles
Build incrementally — MVP first, expand in phases
Every component observable from day one via LangSmith
Claude (Anthropic) as primary reasoning model throughout
Azure as cloud infrastructure backbone
Simplicity over cleverness in early phases



2. Phased Development Plan
Phase 1 — MVP: Chat with Memory (Weeks 1–4)
Goal: A working agent you can talk to that remembers your documents and conversations.

Upload PDF, DOCX, TXT files to a vector store
LangChain document loaders for parsing and chunking
Embeddings stored in Qdrant vector database
Raw files stored in Azure Blob Storage
Conversational RAG — ask questions grounded in your docs
LangGraph orchestrator with retrieval tool
Claude generates answers from retrieved context
Persistent conversation memory across sessions
PostgreSQL stores full conversation history
Recent history injected into each prompt
Basic user profile extraction
Key facts and preferences extracted after each session
Stored and injected into system prompt
Chainlit web UI (supports chat + basic voice)
LangSmith tracing on every interaction

Phase 2 — Voice + Better Memory (Weeks 5–8)
Goal: Natural voice interaction and a memory that actively learns from every conversation.

Voice input via Whisper (OpenAI) transcription
Voice output via ElevenLabs text-to-speech
Memory update agent — extracts and persists insights after each session
Style learning — agent adapts tone and depth to user preferences
Support for URL ingestion (web pages and articles)

Phase 3 — Proactive + Scale (Weeks 9–12)
Goal: Agent surfaces information unprompted and handles hundreds of documents reliably.

Proactive surfacing — scheduled triggers surface relevant docs/insights
Video ingestion — Whisper transcription + chunked vector storage
Structured data ingestion — CSV, JSON, SQL schema awareness
Azure infrastructure hardened for production
Databricks integration for heavy data pipelines (if needed)
Reinforcement learning module via DSPy objective optimization



