4. Data Flows
4.1 Ingestion Flow
User uploads document via Chainlit UI
Raw file stored to Azure Blob Storage
LangChain loader parses file → text chunks
Chunks embedded via Claude or OpenAI embeddings
Embeddings stored in Qdrant vector store
Document metadata (filename, date, tags) stored in PostgreSQL
Full trace logged to LangSmith

4.2 Chat Flow
User sends message via Chainlit
LangGraph orchestrator receives message
Retrieves recent conversation history from PostgreSQL
Semantic search on Qdrant for relevant doc chunks
Builds context window: system prompt + user profile + history + retrieved chunks
Claude generates response
Response returned to Chainlit UI
Full conversation turn saved to PostgreSQL
Full trace (input → retrieval → generation → output) logged to LangSmith

4.3 Memory Update Flow
After each conversation session ends
LangGraph runs memory extraction pass over the session
Claude extracts key facts, preferences, decisions, style cues
New facts merged into user profile in PostgreSQL (dedup + update)
Updated profile injected into system prompt for next session



