9. Week 1 Build Plan
The goal of Week 1 is a working end-to-end loop: upload a document, ask a question, get an answer grounded in that document, with the full trace visible in LangSmith.

Day 1–2: Local Infrastructure
Set up docker-compose with Qdrant + PostgreSQL running locally
Create PostgreSQL schema (conversations, user_profile, documents tables)
Verify both services running and accessible

Day 3: Ingestion Pipeline
Build loaders.py — parse PDF and TXT files with LangChain
Build chunker.py — recursive text splitter with overlap
Build embedder.py — embed chunks and push to Qdrant
Test: upload a PDF, verify chunks appear in Qdrant

Day 4: LangGraph Agent
Build graph.py — minimal LangGraph agent with retrieval tool
Build retrieval_tool.py — Qdrant semantic search
Wire Claude as the LLM via claude.py wrapper
Test: ask a question via Python script, verify grounded answer

Day 5: UI + Observability
Build app.py — Chainlit UI connected to LangGraph agent
Configure LangSmith tracing in langsmith.py
Test: full end-to-end — upload doc in UI, ask question, see trace in LangSmith



